text:
Were it not for a single man – Inquisitor Kryptman – the fate of Tyran might have gone entirely unnoticed. After all, the galaxy is a big place, mysteries are commonplace and the Imperium is as slow to react as only a monolithic bureaucracy can be. Whilst in time many other Inquisitors, including such distinguished names as Czevak, Agmar and Lok, would come to realise the true threat of the Hive Mind, were it not for Kryptman, its very existence would not have been known before it was already too late. Indeed, whether through a quirk of fate or out of some investigative instinct, Kryptman’s decision to personally investigate Tyran’s mysterious silence proved vital to the Imperium’s survival.

